<subSubSection id="C350650B296BFF90DE61FBE7F3E5B440" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF53680296BFF90DE61FBE7F3E5B440" blockId="1.[113,1089,1052,1299]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DE61FBE7F355B560" bold="true" box="[113,363,1052,1075]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="4CB29B65296BFF90DFEAFBE7F043B560" box="[506,637,1052,1075]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" metricValueMax="6.9" metricValueMin="5.9" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" unit="mm" value="6.4" valueMax="6.9" valueMin="5.9">5.9–6.9 mm</quantity>
. Body short-oval, strongly convex (
<figureCitation id="13712A05296BFF90DDE7FBE7F2BEB500" captionStart="Figs 1–4. 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,188,1265,1284]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,219,1250]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[151,1126,219,1250]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–4. 1–2 – Gonioctena (B.) kuatunensis sp. nov., holotype: 1 – dorsal habitus; 2 – head and pronotum. 3–4 – G. (B.) longshengensis sp. nov., holotype: 3 – dorsal habitus; 4 – head and pronotum. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316152" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
). Dorsum reddish-brown with basal margin of pronotum black (
<figureCitation id="13712A05296BFF90DD3EFBC7F1B1B500" box="[814,911,1084,1107]" captionStart="Figs 1–4. 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,188,1265,1284]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,219,1250]" captionTargetId="figure-10@4.[151,1126,219,1250]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–4. 1–2 – Gonioctena (B.) kuatunensis sp. nov., holotype: 1 – dorsal habitus; 2 – head and pronotum. 3–4 – G. (B.) longshengensis sp. nov., holotype: 3 – dorsal habitus; 4 – head and pronotum. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316152" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316152/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Figs 2, 4</figureCitation>
). Venter entirely or largely reddish-brown. Legs black, partially blackish-brown. Aedeagus long and thin, setose apicolaterally, with apical process varying in shape (
<figureCitation id="13712A05296BFF90DCC1FB87F1BCB5C0" box="[721,898,1148,1171]" captionStart="Figs 6–12. 6–7" captionStartId="6.[151,188,1452,1471]" captionTargetBox="[193,1093,222,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[166,1111,191,1436]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 6–12. 6–7 – Gonioctena (B.) kuatunensis sp. nov.: 6 – antenna; 7 – aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). 8–10 – G. (B.) longshengensis sp. nov.: 8 – antenna; 9 – aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views); 10 – spermatheca. 11 – Gonioctena (B.) mauroi Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (after CHO &amp; BOROWIEC 2016a), aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). 12 – G. (B.) medvedevi Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (after CHO &amp; BOROWIEC 2016a), aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). Scale bars = 1.0 mm (except Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316158/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Figs 7, 9, 11–12</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D03296BFF90DD85FB80F3B7B5E0" authority="(Jacoby, 1888)" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis" subGenus="Brachyphytodecta">
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DD85FB80F62FB5C1" box="[917,1041,1147,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Gonioctena</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DA31FB87F60FB5C0" box="[1057,1073,1148,1171]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DE61FB60F2DBB5E0" box="[113,229,1179,1203]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">flavipennis</emphasis>
(Jacoby, 1888)
</taxonomicName>
is almost identical with members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D03296BFF90DD05FB60F1DAB5E0" authorityName="Cho &amp; Borowiec" authorityYear="2016" box="[789,996,1179,1203]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauroi">
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DD05FB60F1DAB5E0" box="[789,996,1179,1203]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Gonioctena mauroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup in body shape and coloration, but differs in its glabrous aedeagus. The most consistent characteristic that differentiates this species-group from other species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D03296BFF90DA00FB27F335B440" authorityName="Bechyne" authorityYear="1948" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Brachyphytodecta">
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DA00FB27F335B440" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Brachyphytodecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is setose aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
