<paragraph id="8BF53680296BFF90DE61FA90F67EB4D1" blockId="1.[113,1089,1387,1570]" box="[113,1088,1387,1410]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<keyLead id="30BB95B5296BFF90DE61FA90F67EB4D1" box="[113,1088,1387,1410]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
1 Apex of aedeagus triangular or subtriangular (
<figureCitation id="13712A05296BFF90DC6BFA90F12FB4D1" box="[635,785,1387,1410]" captionStart="Figs 6–12. 6–7" captionStartId="6.[151,188,1452,1471]" captionTargetBox="[193,1093,222,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[166,1111,191,1436]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 6–12. 6–7 – Gonioctena (B.) kuatunensis sp. nov.: 6 – antenna; 7 – aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). 8–10 – G. (B.) longshengensis sp. nov.: 8 – antenna; 9 – aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views); 10 – spermatheca. 11 – Gonioctena (B.) mauroi Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (after CHO &amp; BOROWIEC 2016a), aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). 12 – G. (B.) medvedevi Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (after CHO &amp; BOROWIEC 2016a), aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). Scale bars = 1.0 mm (except Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316158/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Figs 9, 11–12</figureCitation>
). ....................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF53680296BFF90DE61FA70F67EB4F1" blockId="1.[113,1089,1387,1570]" box="[113,1088,1418,1442]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<keyLead id="30BB95B5296BFF90DE61FA70F67EB4F1" box="[113,1088,1418,1442]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
– Apex of aedeagus semicircular (
<figureCitation id="13712A05296BFF90DFF8FA70F014B4F1" box="[488,554,1419,1442]" captionStart="Figs 6–12. 6–7" captionStartId="6.[151,188,1452,1471]" captionTargetBox="[193,1093,222,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-10@6.[166,1111,191,1436]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 6–12. 6–7 – Gonioctena (B.) kuatunensis sp. nov.: 6 – antenna; 7 – aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). 8–10 – G. (B.) longshengensis sp. nov.: 8 – antenna; 9 – aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views); 10 – spermatheca. 11 – Gonioctena (B.) mauroi Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (after CHO &amp; BOROWIEC 2016a), aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). 12 – G. (B.) medvedevi Cho &amp; Borowiec, 2016 (after CHO &amp; BOROWIEC 2016a), aedeagus, holotype (dorsal and lateral views). Scale bars = 1.0 mm (except Fig. 10 = 0.5 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316158/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). .............................. 
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DD1DFA71F67EB4F1" bold="true" box="[781,1088,1418,1442]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D03296BFF90DD1DFA71F1DAB4F1" authority="Cho, 2017" authorityName="Cho" authorityYear="2017" box="[781,996,1418,1442]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuatunensis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Brachyphytodecta">
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DD1DFA71F11EB4F1" bold="true" box="[781,800,1418,1442]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">G</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DD27FA71F177B4F2" bold="true" box="[823,841,1418,1441]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">B</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="B93EEA92296BFF90DD4FFA71F1DAB4F1" bold="true" box="[863,996,1418,1442]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">kuatunensis</emphasis>
